bcl:definition.bcl:text:
  applicable statutory limitation period means the limitation
period established for a contract by section 23, 76 or 104 of the Act that applies in respect of the
contract;

  credit insurance means insurance against loss to a creditor
if the loss is the result of the insolvency or default of the creditor's
debtor;

  mortgage insurance means insurance against loss caused by
default on the part of a borrower under a loan secured by a mortgage or charge on, or
other security interest in, real property;

